block menu/megamenu
	+sub_section( 'Megamenu', 'megamenu' )
		p With built in simple megamenu functionality you can display child menu (sub-menu) items in columns.

		block menu/megamenu/image/01
			+image( 'https://easycaptures.com/fs/uploaded/1625/7456394390.jpg', 'Megamenu example preview.' )

		ol
			li
				p Set a <code>megamenu</code> class on the parent menu item (1st level menu item).

				block menu/megamenu/image/02
					+image( 'https://easycaptures.com/fs/uploaded/1625/5144473367.png', 'Setting up menu item class.' )

				if true === config.compatibility.megamenu_fullwidth
					+tip( 'Fullwidth megamenu', 'h4' )
						p Add the <code>fullwidth</code> CSS class (so it becomes <code>megamenu fullwidth</code>) to stretch the megamenu full width of the screen.

			li
				p Then the 2nd level menu items (first child menu items) become captions for megamenu columns.

				if false !== config.compatibility.megamenu_disable_link
					+tip( 'Disable link', 'h4' )
						p You can set <code>disable-link</code> CSS class on these menu items to render their link inactive. It is still recommended to set their link to a dummy URL such simple as <code>#0</code> would do.

			li
				p Finally, the 3rd level menu items (second child menu items) become actual menu items within your megamenu columns.
